dellNetBgpM2.name: dellNetBgpM2

revisions.description: This is a Dell Networking OS proprietary version of the draft-ietf-idr-bgp4-mibv2-05.txt MIB as proposed by the IETF Inter-Domain Routing Working Group. This mib will be obsolete when IANA-number is assigned. The following objects are added by Dell. - Added to BgpM2PeerCounterstable dellNetBgpM2PeerInKeepalives, dellNetBgpM2PeerOutKeepalives, dellNetBgpM2PeerInOpen, dellNetBgpM2PeerOutOpen, dellNetBgpM2PeerInRteRefresh, dellNetBgpM2PeerOutRteRefresh - Added to BgpM2PrefixCountersTable dellNetBgpM2PrefixWdrawnByPeer, dellNetBgpM2PrefixWdrawnFromPeer

dellNetBgpM2.description: This MIB module defines management objects for the Border Gateway Protocol, Version 4.

DellNetBgpM2Identifier.name: DellNetBgpM2Identifier
DellNetBgpM2Identifier.description: The representation of a BGP Identifier. The BGP Identifier should be represented in the OCTET STRING as with the first OCTET of the string containing the first OCTET of the BGP Identifier received or sent in the OPEN packet and so on. Even though the BGP Identifier is trending away from an IP address it is still displayed as if it was one, even when it would be an illegal IP address.

DellNetBgpM2Safi.name: DellNetBgpM2Safi
DellNetBgpM2Safi.description: The representation of a BGP SAFI

DellNetBgpM2Community.description: The representation of a BGP Community.

DellNetBgpM2ExtendedCommunity.name: DellNetBgpM2ExtendedCommunity
DellNetBgpM2ExtendedCommunity.description: The representation of a BGP Extended Community.

dellNetBgpM2Established.name: dellNetBgpM2Established
dellNetBgpM2Established.description: The BGP Established event is generated when the BGP FSM enters the ESTABLISHED state.

dellNetBgpM2BackwardTransition.name: dellNetBgpM2BackwardTransition
dellNetBgpM2BackwardTransition.description: The BGPBackwardTransition Event is generated when the BGP FSM moves from a higher numbered state to a lower numbered state.

dellNetBgpM2VersionEntry.name: dellNetBgpM2VersionEntry
dellNetBgpM2VersionEntry.description: Entry containing data on a given supported version of the Border Gateway Protocol and the level of support provided. It is expected that any agent implementation supporting this MIB module will report support for Version 4 of the Border Gateway Protocol at the very minimum.

dellNetBgpM2VersionIndex.name: dellNetBgpM2VersionIndex
dellNetBgpM2VersionIndex.description: The version number of the BGP Protocol.

dellNetBgpM2VersionSupported.name: dellNetBgpM2VersionSupported
dellNetBgpM2VersionSupported.description: This value is TRUE if this version of the BGP protocol identified in 'dellNetBgpM2VersionIndex' is supported. The absence of a row for a particular dellNetBgpM2VersionIndex indicates that that dellNetBgpM2VersionIndex protocol version number is not supported.

dellNetBgpM2CapabilitySupportAvailable.name: dellNetBgpM2CapabilitySupportAvailable
dellNetBgpM2CapabilitySupportAvailable.description: This value is TRUE if capability support is available and is enabled.

dellNetBgpM2SupportedCapabilitiesEntry.name: dellNetBgpM2SupportedCapabilitiesEntry
dellNetBgpM2SupportedCapabilitiesEntry.description: Information about supported capabilities indexed by capability number.

dellNetBgpM2SupportedCapabilityCode.name: dellNetBgpM2SupportedCapabilityCode
dellNetBgpM2SupportedCapabilityCode.description: Index of supported capability. The index directly corresponds with the BGP-4 Capability Advertisement Capability Code.

dellNetBgpM2SupportedCapability.name: dellNetBgpM2SupportedCapability
dellNetBgpM2SupportedCapability.description: This value is True if this capability is supported, False otherwise.

dellNetBgpM2AsSize.name: dellNetBgpM2AsSize
dellNetBgpM2AsSize.description: The size of the AS value in this implementation. The semantics of this are determined as per the as-4bytes draft.

dellNetBgpM2LocalAs.name: dellNetBgpM2LocalAs
dellNetBgpM2LocalAs.description: The local autonomous system number. If the dellNetBgpM2AsSize is twoOctet, then the range is constrained to be 0-65535.

dellNetBgpM2LocalIdentifier.name: dellNetBgpM2LocalIdentifier
dellNetBgpM2LocalIdentifier.description: The BGP Identifier of local system. Current practice is trending away from this value being treated as an IP address and more as a generic identifier.

dellNetBgpM2RouteReflector.name: dellNetBgpM2RouteReflector
dellNetBgpM2RouteReflector.description: This value is TRUE if this implementation supports the BGP Route Reflection Extension and is enabled as a route reflector. If the BGP Route Reflection extension is not supported this value must be FALSE.

dellNetBgpM2ClusterId.name: dellNetBgpM2ClusterId
dellNetBgpM2ClusterId.description: The configured Cluster-ID of the BGP Speaker. This will default to the BGP Speaker's DellNetBgpM2Identifier if this speaker is functioning as a route reflector and an explicit Cluster-ID has not been configured. A value of 0.0.0.0 will be present if Route Reflection is not enabled.

dellNetBgpM2ConfederationRouter.reference: RFC 3065 - Autonomous System Confederations for BGP
dellNetBgpM2ConfederationRouter.description: This value is TRUE if this implementation supports the BGP AS Confederations Extension and this router is configured to be in a confederation.

dellNetBgpM2ConfederationId.name: dellNetBgpM2ConfederationId
dellNetBgpM2ConfederationId.reference: RFC 3065 - Autonomous System Confederations for BGP
dellNetBgpM2ConfederationId.description: The local Confederation Identification Number. This value will be zero (0) if this BGP Speaker is not a confederation router.

dellNetBgpM2CfgBaseScalarStorageType.name: dellNetBgpM2CfgBaseScalarStorageType
dellNetBgpM2CfgBaseScalarStorageType.description: This object specifies the intended storage type for all configurable base scalars.

dellNetBgpM2CfgLocalAs.name: dellNetBgpM2CfgLocalAs
dellNetBgpM2CfgLocalAs.description: The local autonomous system number. If the dellNetBgpM2AsSize is twoOctet, then the range is constrained to be 0-65535.

dellNetBgpM2CfgLocalIdentifier.name: dellNetBgpM2CfgLocalIdentifier
dellNetBgpM2CfgLocalIdentifier.description: The BGP Identifier of local system. Current practice is trending away from this value being treated as an IP address and more as a generic identifier.

dellNetBgpM2CfgRouteReflector.name: dellNetBgpM2CfgRouteReflector

dellNetBgpM2CfgClusterId.name: dellNetBgpM2CfgClusterId

This will default to the BGP Speaker's DellNetBgpM2Identifier if this speaker is functioning as a route reflector and an explicit Cluster-ID has not been configured. A value of 0.0.0.0 will be present if Route Reflection is not enabled.

dellNetBgpM2CfgConfederationRouter.name: dellNetBgpM2CfgConfederationRouter
dellNetBgpM2CfgConfederationRouter.reference: RFC 3065 - Autonomous System Confederations for BGP
dellNetBgpM2CfgConfederationRouter.description: This value is set to true if this implementation will be supporting BGP AS Confederations.

dellNetBgpM2CfgConfederationId.name: dellNetBgpM2CfgConfederationId
dellNetBgpM2CfgConfederationId.reference: RFC 3065 - Autonomous System Confederations for BGP
dellNetBgpM2CfgConfederationId.description: The local Confederation Identification Number. This value will be zero (0) if this BGP Speaker is not a confederation router.

dellNetBgpM2PeerTable.name: dellNetBgpM2PeerTable
dellNetBgpM2PeerTable.description: BGP peer table. This table contains, one entry per remote BGP peer, any information about the connections with the remote BGP peers.

dellNetBgpM2PeerEntry.name: dellNetBgpM2PeerEntry
dellNetBgpM2PeerEntry.description: Entry containing information about the connection with a remote BGP peer.

dellNetBgpM2PeerInstance.name: dellNetBgpM2PeerInstance
dellNetBgpM2PeerInstance.description: The routing instance index. Some BGP implementations permit the creation of multiple instances of a BGP routing process. An example includes RFC 2547 PE-CE routers. Implementations that do not support multiple routing instances should return 1 for this object. XXX TODO - We need to provide a way to configure these in the peer configuration table.

dellNetBgpM2PeerIdentifier.name: dellNetBgpM2PeerIdentifier
dellNetBgpM2PeerIdentifier.description: The BGP Identifier of this entry's remote BGP peer. This entry should be 0.0.0.0 unless the dellNetBgpM2PeerState is in the OpenConfirm or the Established state.

dellNetBgpM2PeerState.name: dellNetBgpM2PeerState
dellNetBgpM2PeerState.description: The remote BGP peer's FSM state.

dellNetBgpM2PeerStatus.name: dellNetBgpM2PeerStatus
dellNetBgpM2PeerStatus.description: Whether or not the BGP FSM for this remote peer is halted or running. The BGP FSM for a remote peer is halted after processing a Stop event. Likewise, it is in the running state after a Start event. The dellNetBgpM2PeerState will generally be in the idle state when the FSM is halted, although some extensions such as Graceful Restart will leave the peer in the Idle state but with the FSM running.

dellNetBgpM2PeerConfiguredVersion.name: dellNetBgpM2PeerConfiguredVersion
dellNetBgpM2PeerConfiguredVersion.description: The configured version to originally start with this remote peer. The BGP speaker may permit negotiation to a lower version number of the protocol.

dellNetBgpM2PeerNegotiatedVersion.name: dellNetBgpM2PeerNegotiatedVersion
dellNetBgpM2PeerNegotiatedVersion.description: The negotiated version of BGP running between the two peers.

dellNetBgpM2PeerLocalAddrType.name: dellNetBgpM2PeerLocalAddrType
dellNetBgpM2PeerLocalAddrType.description: The address family of the local end of the peering session.

dellNetBgpM2PeerLocalAddr.name: dellNetBgpM2PeerLocalAddr
dellNetBgpM2PeerLocalAddr.description: The address of the local end of the peering session.

dellNetBgpM2PeerLocalPort.name: dellNetBgpM2PeerLocalPort
dellNetBgpM2PeerLocalPort.description: The local port for the TCP connection between the BGP peers.

dellNetBgpM2PeerLocalAs.name: dellNetBgpM2PeerLocalAs
dellNetBgpM2PeerLocalAs.description: Some implementations of BGP can represent themselves as multiple ASs. This is the AS that this peering session is representing itself as to the remote peer.

dellNetBgpM2PeerRemoteAddrType.name: dellNetBgpM2PeerRemoteAddrType
dellNetBgpM2PeerRemoteAddrType.description: The address family of the remote end of the peering session.

dellNetBgpM2PeerRemoteAddr.name: dellNetBgpM2PeerRemoteAddr
dellNetBgpM2PeerRemoteAddr.description: The address of the remote end of the peering session.

dellNetBgpM2PeerRemotePort.name: dellNetBgpM2PeerRemotePort
dellNetBgpM2PeerRemotePort.reference: RFC 2012 - SNMPv2 Management Information Base for the Transmission Control Protocol using SMIv2. RFC 2542 - IP Version 6 Management Information Base for the Transmission Control Protocol.
dellNetBgpM2PeerRemotePort.description: The remote port for the TCP connection between the BGP peers. In the case of a transport for which the notion of 'port' is irrelevant, an instance value of -1 should be returned by the agent for this object. Note that the objects dellNetBgpM2PeerLocalAddr, dellNetBgpM2PeerLocalPort, dellNetBgpM2PeerRemoteAddr and dellNetBgpM2PeerRemotePort provide the appropriate reference to the standard MIB TCP connection table. or even the ipv6 TCP MIB as in rfc2452.

dellNetBgpM2PeerIndex.name: dellNetBgpM2PeerIndex
dellNetBgpM2PeerIndex.description: This value is a unique index for the remote peer entry in the dellNetBgpM2PeerTable. It is assigned by the agent at the point of creation of the dellNetBgpM2PeerTable row entry. While its value is guaranteed to be unique at any time, it is otherwise opaque to the management application with respect to its value or the contiguity of dellNetBgpM2PeerIndex row instance values across rows of the dellNetBgpM2PeerTable. It is used to provide an index structure for other tables whose data is logically per-peer. For explicitly configured peers, this value will remain consistent until this row is deleted by deleting the configured peers. Unconfigured peers will generate a monotonically increasing number when a BGP FSM is built to process the peering session. Values in the dellNetBgpM2PeerTable and other tables utilizing dellNetBgpM2PeerIndex are expected to remain in existence for an arbitrary time after the unconfigured peer has been deleted in order to allow management applications to extract useful management information for those peers. Thus, an unconfigured peer using the same indices as the dellNetBgpM2PeerTable that comes up while this row still exists will re-utilize the same row.

dellNetBgpM2PeerErrorsTable.name: dellNetBgpM2PeerErrorsTable
dellNetBgpM2PeerErrorsTable.description: On a per peer basis, this table reflects the last protocol-defined error encountered and reported on the peer session. If no entry for a given peer, by its dellNetBgpM2PeerIndex, exists in this table, then no such errors have been observed, reported, and recorded on the session.

dellNetBgpM2PeerErrorsEntry.name: dellNetBgpM2PeerErrorsEntry
dellNetBgpM2PeerErrorsEntry.description: Each entry contains information about errors sent and received for a particular BGP peer.

dellNetBgpM2PeerLastErrorReceived.name: dellNetBgpM2PeerLastErrorReceived
dellNetBgpM2PeerLastErrorReceived.description: The last error code and subcode received by this BGP Speaker via a NOTIFICATION message for this peer. If no error has occurred, this field is zero. Otherwise, the first byte of this two byte OCTET STRING contains the error code, and the second byte contains the subcode.

dellNetBgpM2PeerLastErrorSent.name: dellNetBgpM2PeerLastErrorSent
dellNetBgpM2PeerLastErrorSent.description: The last error code and subcode sent by this BGP Speaker via a NOTIFICATION message to this peer. If no error has occurred, this field is zero. Otherwise, the first byte of this two byte OCTET STRING contains the error code, and the second byte contains the subcode.

dellNetBgpM2PeerLastErrorReceivedTime.name: dellNetBgpM2PeerLastErrorReceivedTime
dellNetBgpM2PeerLastErrorReceivedTime.description: The timestamp that the last NOTIFICATION was received from this peer.

dellNetBgpM2PeerLastErrorSentTime.name: dellNetBgpM2PeerLastErrorSentTime
dellNetBgpM2PeerLastErrorSentTime.description: The timestamp that the last NOTIFICATION was sent to this peer.

dellNetBgpM2PeerLastErrorReceivedText.name: dellNetBgpM2PeerLastErrorReceivedText
dellNetBgpM2PeerLastErrorReceivedText.description: This object contains an implementation specific explanation of the error that was reported.

dellNetBgpM2PeerLastErrorSentText.name: dellNetBgpM2PeerLastErrorSentText
dellNetBgpM2PeerLastErrorSentText.description: This object contains an implementation specific explanation of the error that is being reported.

dellNetBgpM2PeerLastErrorReceivedData.name: dellNetBgpM2PeerLastErrorReceivedData
dellNetBgpM2PeerLastErrorReceivedData.description: The last error code's data seen by this peer.

dellNetBgpM2PeerLastErrorSentData.name: dellNetBgpM2PeerLastErrorSentData
dellNetBgpM2PeerLastErrorSentData.description: The last error code's data sent to this peer.

dellNetBgpM2PeerEventTimesTable.name: dellNetBgpM2PeerEventTimesTable
dellNetBgpM2PeerEventTimesTable.description: A table reporting the per-peering session amount of time elapsed and update events since the peering session advanced into the Established state.

dellNetBgpM2PeerEventTimesEntry.name: dellNetBgpM2PeerEventTimesEntry
dellNetBgpM2PeerEventTimesEntry.description: Each row contains a set of statistics about time spent and events encountered in the peer session Established state.

dellNetBgpM2PeerFsmEstablishedTime.name: dellNetBgpM2PeerFsmEstablishedTime
dellNetBgpM2PeerFsmEstablishedTime.description: This timer indicates how long (in seconds) this peer has been in the Established state or how long since this peer was last in the Established state. It is set to zero when a new peer is configured or the router is booted.

dellNetBgpM2PeerInUpdatesElapsedTime.name: dellNetBgpM2PeerInUpdatesElapsedTime
dellNetBgpM2PeerInUpdatesElapsedTime.description: Elapsed time in seconds since the last BGP UPDATE message was received from the peer. Each time dellNetBgpM2PeerInUpdates is incremented, the value of this object is set to zero (0). This value shall also be zero (0) when the peer is not in the Established state

dellNetBgpM2PeerConfiguredTimersTable.name: dellNetBgpM2PeerConfiguredTimersTable
dellNetBgpM2PeerConfiguredTimersTable.description: Per peer management data on BGP session timers.

dellNetBgpM2PeerConfiguredTimersEntry.name: dellNetBgpM2PeerConfiguredTimersEntry
dellNetBgpM2PeerConfiguredTimersEntry.description: Each entry corresponds to the current state of BGP timers on a given peering session.

dellNetBgpM2PeerConnectRetryInterval.name: dellNetBgpM2PeerConnectRetryInterval
dellNetBgpM2PeerConnectRetryInterval.description: Time interval in seconds for the ConnectRetry timer. The suggested value for this timer is 120 seconds.

dellNetBgpM2PeerHoldTimeConfigured.name: dellNetBgpM2PeerHoldTimeConfigured
dellNetBgpM2PeerHoldTimeConfigured.description: Time interval in seconds for the Hold Time configured for this BGP speaker with this peer. This value is placed in an OPEN message sent to this peer by this BGP speaker, and is compared with the Hold Time field in an OPEN message received from the peer when determining the Hold Time (dellNetBgpM2PeerHoldTime) with the peer. This value must not be less than three seconds if it is not zero (0) in which case the Hold Time is NOT to be established with the peer. The suggested value for this timer is 90 seconds.

dellNetBgpM2PeerKeepAliveConfigured.name: dellNetBgpM2PeerKeepAliveConfigured
dellNetBgpM2PeerKeepAliveConfigured.description: Time interval in seconds for the KeepAlive timer configured for this BGP speaker with this peer. The value of this object will only determine the KEEPALIVE messages frequency relative to the value specified in dellNetBgpM2PeerHoldTimeConfigured; the actual time interval for the KEEPALIVE messages is indicated by dellNetBgpM2PeerKeepAlive. A reasonable maximum value for this timer would be configured to be one third of that of dellNetBgpM2PeerHoldTimeConfigured. If the value of this object is zero (0), no periodical KEEPALIVE messages are sent to the peer after the BGP connection has been established. The suggested value for this timer is 30 seconds.

dellNetBgpM2PeerMinASOrigInterval.name: dellNetBgpM2PeerMinASOrigInterval
dellNetBgpM2PeerMinASOrigInterval.description: Time interval in seconds for the MinASOriginationInterval timer. The suggested value for this timer is 15 seconds.

dellNetBgpM2PeerMinRouteAdverInterval.name: dellNetBgpM2PeerMinRouteAdverInterval
dellNetBgpM2PeerMinRouteAdverInterval.description: Time interval in seconds for the MinRouteAdvertisementInterval timer. The suggested value for this timer is 30 seconds.

dellNetBgpM2PeerNegotiatedTimersTable.name: dellNetBgpM2PeerNegotiatedTimersTable
dellNetBgpM2PeerNegotiatedTimersTable.description: Current values of per-peer timers which can be dynamically set in the dellNetBgpM2PeerConfiguredTimersTable. Values reflected in this table are the current operational values, after negotiation from values derived from initial configuration or last set from dellNetBgpM2PeerConfiguredTimersTable row instances.

dellNetBgpM2PeerNegotiatedTimersEntry.name: dellNetBgpM2PeerNegotiatedTimersEntry
dellNetBgpM2PeerNegotiatedTimersEntry.description: Each entry reflects a value of the currently operational, negotiated timers as reflected in the DellNetBgpM2PeerNegotiatedTimersEntry.

dellNetBgpM2PeerHoldTime.name: dellNetBgpM2PeerHoldTime
dellNetBgpM2PeerHoldTime.description: The value of this object is calculated by this BGP Speaker as being; zero (0) - if this was the value sent by the peer and this value is permitted by this BGP Speaker. In this case, no keepalive messages are sent and the Hold Timer is not set. At least three (3). This value is the smaller of the value sent by this peer in the OPEN message and dellNetBgpM2PeerHoldTimeConfigured for this peer. This value is only defined when the peering session is in the Established state.

dellNetBgpM2PeerKeepAlive.name: dellNetBgpM2PeerKeepAlive
dellNetBgpM2PeerKeepAlive.description: Time interval in seconds for the KeepAlive timer established with the peer. The value of this object is calculated by this BGP speaker such that, when compared with dellNetBgpM2PeerHoldTime, it has the same proportion as what dellNetBgpM2PeerKeepAliveConfigured has when compared with dellNetBgpM2PeerHoldTimeConfigured. If the value of this object is zero (0), it indicates that the KeepAlive timer has not been established with the peer, or, the value of dellNetBgpM2PeerKeepAliveConfigured is zero (0). This value is only defined when the peering session is in the Established state.

dellNetBgpM2PeerCapsAnnouncedTable.name: dellNetBgpM2PeerCapsAnnouncedTable
dellNetBgpM2PeerCapsAnnouncedTable.description: This table contains the capabilities that are supported for a given peer.

dellNetBgpM2PeerCapsAnnouncedEntry.description: These entries are keyed by a BGP-4 peer remote address and the BGP Capability Code

dellNetBgpM2PeerCapAnnouncedCode.description: The BGP Capability Advertisement Capability Code.

dellNetBgpM2PeerCapAnnouncedIndex.description: Multiple instances of a given capability may be sent bgp a BGP speaker. This variable is used to index them.

dellNetBgpM2PeerCapAnnouncedValue.description: The value of the announced capability.

dellNetBgpM2PeerCapsReceivedTable.name: dellNetBgpM2PeerCapsReceivedTable
dellNetBgpM2PeerCapsReceivedTable.description: This table contains the capabilities that are supported for a given peer.

dellNetBgpM2PeerCapsReceivedEntry.name: dellNetBgpM2PeerCapsReceivedEntry
dellNetBgpM2PeerCapsReceivedEntry.description: These entries are keyed by a BGP-4 peer remote address and the BGP Capability Code

dellNetBgpM2PeerCapReceivedCode.name: dellNetBgpM2PeerCapReceivedCode
dellNetBgpM2PeerCapReceivedCode.description: The BGP Capability Advertisement Capability Code.

dellNetBgpM2PeerCapReceivedIndex.name: dellNetBgpM2PeerCapReceivedIndex
dellNetBgpM2PeerCapReceivedIndex.description: Multiple instances of a given capability may be sent bgp a BGP speaker. This variable is used to index them.

dellNetBgpM2PeerCapReceivedValue.name: dellNetBgpM2PeerCapReceivedValue
dellNetBgpM2PeerCapReceivedValue.description: The value of the announced capability.

dellNetBgpM2PeerCountersTable.name: dellNetBgpM2PeerCountersTable
dellNetBgpM2PeerCountersTable.description: The counters associated with a BGP Peer.

dellNetBgpM2PeerCountersEntry.name: dellNetBgpM2PeerCountersEntry
dellNetBgpM2PeerCountersEntry.description: Each entry contains counters of message transmissions and FSM transitions for a given BGP Peering session.

dellNetBgpM2PeerInUpdates.name: dellNetBgpM2PeerInUpdates
dellNetBgpM2PeerInUpdates.description: The number of BGP UPDATE messages received on this connection. This object should be initialized to zero (0) when the connection is established.

dellNetBgpM2PeerOutUpdates.name: dellNetBgpM2PeerOutUpdates
dellNetBgpM2PeerOutUpdates.description: The number of BGP UPDATE messages transmitted on this connection. This object should be initialized to zero (0) when the connection is established.

dellNetBgpM2PeerInTotalMessages.name: dellNetBgpM2PeerInTotalMessages
dellNetBgpM2PeerInTotalMessages.description: The total number of messages received from the remote peer on this connection. This object should be initialized to zero when the connection is established.

dellNetBgpM2PeerOutTotalMessages.name: dellNetBgpM2PeerOutTotalMessages
dellNetBgpM2PeerOutTotalMessages.description: The total number of messages transmitted to the remote peer on this connection. This object should be initialized to zero when the connection is established.

dellNetBgpM2PeerFsmEstablishedTrans.name: dellNetBgpM2PeerFsmEstablishedTrans
dellNetBgpM2PeerFsmEstablishedTrans.description: The total number of times the BGP FSM transitioned into the established state for this peer.

dellNetBgpM2PeerInKeepalives.description: The number of Keepalive messages received from a peer.Implemented by Dell.

dellNetBgpM2PeerOutKeepalives.name: dellNetBgpM2PeerOutKeepalives

dellNetBgpM2PeerInOpen.description: The number of Open messages received from a peer. Implemented by Dell.

dellNetBgpM2PeerOutOpen.name: dellNetBgpM2PeerOutOpen
dellNetBgpM2PeerOutOpen.description: The number of Open messages sent to a peer. Implemented by Dell.

dellNetBgpM2PeerInRteRefresh.name: dellNetBgpM2PeerInRteRefresh
dellNetBgpM2PeerInRteRefresh.description: The number of Route Refresh messages received from a peer. Implemented by Dell.

dellNetBgpM2PeerOutRteRefresh.name: dellNetBgpM2PeerOutRteRefresh
dellNetBgpM2PeerOutRteRefresh.description: The number of Route Refresh messages sent to a peer. Implemented by Dell.

dellNetBgpM2PrefixCountersSafi.description: The SAFI index of the per-peer, per prefix counters

dellNetBgpM2PrefixWdrawnByPeer.description: The number of prefixes withdrawn by a peer. Implemened by Dell.

dellNetBgpM2PrefixWdrawnFromPeer.name: dellNetBgpM2PrefixWdrawnFromPeer
dellNetBgpM2PrefixWdrawnFromPeer.description: The number of prefixes withdrawn from a peer. Implemened by Dell.

dellNetBgpM2PeerReflectorClientTable.name: dellNetBgpM2PeerReflectorClientTable
dellNetBgpM2PeerReflectorClientTable.description: Table of route reflection client settings on a per-peer basis.

dellNetBgpM2PeerReflectorClientEntry.name: dellNetBgpM2PeerReflectorClientEntry
dellNetBgpM2PeerReflectorClientEntry.description: Entry containing data on a per-peer basis on whether the peer is configured as a route reflector client.

dellNetBgpM2PeerReflectorClient.name: dellNetBgpM2PeerReflectorClient
dellNetBgpM2PeerReflectorClient.description: This value indicates whether the given peer is a reflector client of this router, or not. A value of nonClient indicates that this peer is not a reflector client. A value of client indicates that this peer is a reflector client that is not fully meshed with other reflector clients. A value of meshedClient indicates that the peer is a reflector client and is fully meshed with all other reflector clients. This value must be nonClient (0) for BGP external peers.

dellNetBgpM2PeerConfedMemberTable.name: dellNetBgpM2PeerConfedMemberTable
dellNetBgpM2PeerConfedMemberTable.description: Table of confederation member settings on a per-peer basis.

dellNetBgpM2PeerConfedMemberEntry.name: dellNetBgpM2PeerConfedMemberEntry
dellNetBgpM2PeerConfedMemberEntry.description: Entry containing data on a per-peer basis on whether the peer is configured as a BGP confederation member.

dellNetBgpM2PeerConfedMember.name: dellNetBgpM2PeerConfedMember
dellNetBgpM2PeerConfedMember.description: This value indicates whether the given peer is in our confederation or not.

dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerAdminStatusTable.name: dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerAdminStatusTable
dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerAdminStatusTable.description: Table containing rows for administratively starting and stopping peering sessions.

dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerAdminStatusEntry.name: dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerAdminStatusEntry
dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerAdminStatusEntry.description: Entry containing row for administratively starting and stopping peers.

dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerAdminStatus.name: dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerAdminStatus
dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerAdminStatus.description: This object allows the Manual Stop and Manual Start events to be sent to an activated peering session.

dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerNextIndex.name: dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerNextIndex
dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerNextIndex.description: This object contains the next appropriate value to use as an index for creation of a row instance in in the dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerTable. If the number of available entries in the dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerTable is exhausted, a retrieval value of this object instance will return 0. A value of 0 may also be returned if the agent is otherwise incapable of dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerTable row creation at the time of dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerNextIndex retrieval.

dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerTable.name: dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerTable
dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerTable.description: BGP configuration peer table. This table allows the configuration of the parameters for a session with a BGP peer. +++wayne provide description of how config should be done for a peer per table.

dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerEntry.name: dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerEntry
dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerEntry.description: Entry containing information set up by a management entity to configure a connection with a BGP peer.

dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerConfiguredVersion.name: dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerConfiguredVersion
dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerConfiguredVersion.description: The configured version to originally start with this peer. The BGP speaker may permit negotiation to a lower version number of the protocol depending on the set value of dellNetBgpM2CfgAllowVersionNegotiation.

dellNetBgpM2CfgAllowVersionNegotiation.name: dellNetBgpM2CfgAllowVersionNegotiation
dellNetBgpM2CfgAllowVersionNegotiation.description: If set to true, during session establishment with this peer, negotiation to a version lower than that specified in dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerConfiguredVersion will be allowed.

dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerLocalAddrType.name: dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerLocalAddrType
dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerLocalAddrType.description: The address family of the speakers of this BGP session.

dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerLocalAddr.name: dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerLocalAddr
dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerLocalAddr.description: The address of the local end of the peering session.

dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerLocalAs.name: dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerLocalAs
dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerLocalAs.description: Autonomous system represented to peer on peering session initialization. Some implementations of BGP can represent themselves as multiple ASes. These implementations can set this to an alternate autonomous system. If this object is set to zero (0) at the point this row instance is set to active, then the implementation will initialize this session representing itself as the value of dellNetBgpM2CfgLocalAs.

dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerRemoteAddrType.name: dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerRemoteAddrType
dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerRemoteAddrType.description: The address family of the speakers of the remote BGP session.

dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerRemoteAddr.name: dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerRemoteAddr
dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerRemoteAddr.description: The address of the remote end (destination address of peer) for peering session.

dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerRemoteAs.name: dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerRemoteAs
dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerRemoteAs.description: Autonomous system number of the remote peer.

dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerEntryStorageType.name: dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerEntryStorageType
dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerEntryStorageType.description: This object type specifies the intended storage type for the dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerEntry row instance.

dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerError.name: dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerError
dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerError.description: This value indicates the current error status of the row denoting the configured error status. If this row is still under creation (has not been activated dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerRowEntryStatus), then this instance will be set to not-activated (1). At the point that the row is activated, dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerError will reflect the error status of the row data itself. If there is another session already activated with the same local and remote addresses as denoted by {dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerLocalAddrType, dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerLocalAddr, dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerRemoteAddr}, then the value of this will be set to err-duplicate-peering-session (2). If this row is associated with a peer session whose initialization has been attempted, the value will be set to activated (3) (and, dellNetBgpM2PeerCfgPeerEntry will be set to the row instance of the entry in the dellNetBgpM2PeerTable which reflects the state of the peering session). Note that this object only reflects the error as a function of the attempted activation of this row as containing data for a bgp peering session. The actual state of the session at the point of any protocol exchange or session state machine initiation is reflected in the dellNetBgpM2PeerTable row instance (as reflected through dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerPeerEntry) associated with this row instance.

dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerBgpPeerEntry.name: dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerBgpPeerEntry
dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerBgpPeerEntry.description: Upon activation of the session data contained in this row instance, this object points to an instance of a row within the dellNetBgpM2PeerTable reflecting the session in its initializing or operational state. Retrieval of this column instance will always yield a value of {0.0} unless the session has successfully been activated (via dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerRowEntryStatus). Such row instances will always have a value of dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerError which is activated (3).

dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerRowEntryStatus.name: dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerRowEntryStatus
dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerRowEntryStatus.description: This object type is used to control creation, activation, and deletion of this row instance.

dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerIndex.name: dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerIndex
dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerIndex.description: Uniquely identifies an instance of a peer row, as an element of configuration.

dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerStatus.name: dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerStatus
dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerStatus.description: This specifies the state of the peering session upon activation. If disabled, the FSM is in the halted state and no Automatic Start events are generated. If enabled, the FSM is in the running state and Automatic Start events may be generated.

dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerTimersTable.name: dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerTimersTable
dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerTimersTable.description: Table for configuration of per-peer timers.

dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerConnectRetryInterval.name: dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerConnectRetryInterval
dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerConnectRetryInterval.description: Time interval in seconds for the ConnectRetry timer. The suggested value for this timer is 120 seconds.

dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerHoldTimeConfigured.name: dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerHoldTimeConfigured
dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerHoldTimeConfigured.description: Time interval in seconds for the Hold Time configured for this BGP speaker with this peer. This value is placed in an OPEN message sent to this peer by this BGP speaker, and is compared with the Hold Time field in an OPEN message received from the peer when determining the Hold Time (dellNetBgpM2PeerHoldTime) with the peer. This value must not be less than three seconds if it is not zero (0) in which case the Hold Time is NOT to be established with the peer. The suggested value for this timer is 90 seconds.

dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerKeepAliveConfigured.name: dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerKeepAliveConfigured
dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerKeepAliveConfigured.description: Time interval in seconds for the KeepAlive timer configured for this BGP speaker with this peer. The value of this object will only determine the KEEPALIVE messages frequency relative to the value specified in dellNetBgpM2PeerHoldTimeConfigured; the actual time interval for the KEEPALIVE messages is indicated by dellNetBgpM2PeerKeepAlive. A reasonable maximum value for this timer would be configured to be one third of that of dellNetBgpM2PeerHoldTimeConfigured. If the value of this object is zero (0), no periodical KEEPALIVE messages are sent to the peer after the BGP connection has been established. The suggested value for this timer is 30 seconds.

dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerMinASOrigInterval.name: dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerMinASOrigInterval
dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerMinASOrigInterval.description: Time interval in seconds for the MinASOriginationInterval timer. The suggested value for this timer is 15 seconds.

dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerMinRouteAdverInter.name: dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerMinRouteAdverInter
dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerMinRouteAdverInter.description: Time interval in seconds for the MinRouteAdvertisementInterval timer. The suggested value for this timer is 30 seconds.

dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerReflectorClientTable.name: dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerReflectorClientTable
dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerReflectorClientTable.description: Table of route reflection client settings on a per-peer basis.

dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerReflectorClientEntry.name: dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerReflectorClientEntry
dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerReflectorClientEntry.description: Entry containing data on a per-peer basis on whether the peer is configured as a route reflector client.

dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerReflectorClient.name: dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerReflectorClient
dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerReflectorClient.description: This value indicates whether the given peer is a reflector client of this router, or not. A value of nonClient indicates that this peer is not a reflector client. A value of client indicates that this peer is a reflector client that is not fully meshed with other reflector clients. A value of meshedClient indicates that the peer is a reflector client and is fully meshed with all other reflector clients. This value must be nonClient (0) for BGP external peers.

dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerConfedMemberTable.name: dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerConfedMemberTable
dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerConfedMemberTable.description: Table of confederation member settings on a per-peer basis.

dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerConfedMemberEntry.name: dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerConfedMemberEntry
dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerConfedMemberEntry.description: Entry containing data on a per-peer basis on whether the peer is configured as a BGP confederation member.

dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerConfedMember.name: dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerConfedMember
dellNetBgpM2CfgPeerConfedMember.description: This value indicates whether the given peer is in our confederation or not.

dellNetBgpM2NlriTable.name: dellNetBgpM2NlriTable
dellNetBgpM2NlriTable.description: The BGP-4 Received Path Attribute Table contains information about paths to destination networks received from all BGP4 peers. Collectively, this represents the Adj-Ribs-In. The route where dellNetBgpM2NlriBest is TRUE represents, for this NLRI, the route that is installed in the LocRib from the Adj-Ribs-In.

dellNetBgpM2NlriEntry.name: dellNetBgpM2NlriEntry
dellNetBgpM2NlriEntry.description: Information about a path to a network.

dellNetBgpM2NlriIndex.name: dellNetBgpM2NlriIndex
dellNetBgpM2NlriIndex.reference: RFC 3107 - Carrying Label Information in BGP-4
dellNetBgpM2NlriIndex.description: This index allows for multiple instances of a base prefix for a certain AFI SAFI from a given peer. This is currently useful for two things: 1. Allowing for a peer in future implementations to send more than a single route instance. 2. Allow for extensions which extend the NLRI field to send the same prefix while utilizing other extension specific information. An example of this is RFC 3107 - Carrying MPLS labels in BGP.

dellNetBgpM2NlriAfi.name: dellNetBgpM2NlriAfi
dellNetBgpM2NlriAfi.description: The address family of the prefix for this NLRI.

dellNetBgpM2NlriSafi.name: dellNetBgpM2NlriSafi
dellNetBgpM2NlriSafi.description: The subsequent address family of the prefix for this NLRI

dellNetBgpM2NlriPrefixType.name: dellNetBgpM2NlriPrefixType
dellNetBgpM2NlriPrefixType.description: The type of the IP address prefix in the Network Layer Reachability Information field. The value of this object is derived from the appropriate value from the dellNetBgpM2NlriAfi field. Where an appropriate InetAddressType is not available, the value of the object must be unknown(0). XXX TODO - This seems like a hack.

dellNetBgpM2NlriPrefix.name: dellNetBgpM2NlriPrefix
dellNetBgpM2NlriPrefix.description: An IP address prefix in the Network Layer Reachability Information field. This object is an IP address containing the prefix with length specified by dellNetBgpM2PathAttrAddrPrefixLen. Any bits beyond the length specified by dellNetBgpM2PathAttrAddrPrefixLen are zeroed.

dellNetBgpM2NlriPrefixLen.name: dellNetBgpM2NlriPrefixLen
dellNetBgpM2NlriPrefixLen.description: Length in bits of the address prefix in the Network Layer Reachability Information field.

dellNetBgpM2NlriBest.name: dellNetBgpM2NlriBest
dellNetBgpM2NlriBest.description: An indication of whether or not this route was chosen as the best BGP4 route.

dellNetBgpM2NlriCalcLocalPref.name: dellNetBgpM2NlriCalcLocalPref
dellNetBgpM2NlriCalcLocalPref.description: The degree of preference calculated by the receiving BGP4 speaker for an advertised route.

dellNetBgpM2PathAttrIndex.name: dellNetBgpM2PathAttrIndex
dellNetBgpM2PathAttrIndex.description: This value is a unique index for the per-NLRI entry in the dellNetBgpM2PathAttrTable. It is assigned by the agent at the point of creation of the dellNetBgpM2PathAttrTable row entry. While its value is guaranteed to be unique at any time, it is otherwise opaque to the management application with respect to its value or the contiguity of dellNetBgpM2PathAttrIndex row instance values across rows of the dellNetBgpM2PeerAttrTable. It is used to provide an index structure for other tables whose data is logically per-peer, per-NLRI.

dellNetBgpM2NlriOpaqueType.name: dellNetBgpM2NlriOpaqueType
dellNetBgpM2NlriOpaqueType.reference: RFC 3107 - Carrying Label Information in BGP-4 draft-ietf-mpls-lsr-mib-08.txt
dellNetBgpM2NlriOpaqueType.description: This object enumerates the type of the row that is pointed to in the table row dellNetBgpM2NlriOpaquePointer instance, if dellNetBgpM2NlriOpaquePointer is in fact not a zero length. dellNetBgpM2NlriOpaqueType is necessary since the data referenced by dellNetBgpM2NlriOpaquePointer is opaque to BGP. For example, in the case of RFC 3107, the label stack that is pointed to may occur in the mplsLabelStackTable from the MPLS-LSR-MIB, and the instance value of dellNetBgpM2NlriOpaqueType would be bgpMplsLabelStack(1).

dellNetBgpM2NlriOpaquePointer.name: dellNetBgpM2NlriOpaquePointer
dellNetBgpM2NlriOpaquePointer.description: Pointer to a row that decomposes the data that is opaque to the BGP MIB but is sent in the NLRI. This RowPointer has zero (0) length data instance if dellNetBgpM2NlriOpaqueType is none.

dellNetBgpM2AdjRibsOutTable.name: dellNetBgpM2AdjRibsOutTable
dellNetBgpM2AdjRibsOutTable.description: This table contains on a per-peer basis one or more routes from the dellNetBgpM2NlriTable that have been placed in this peer's Adj-Ribs-Out.

dellNetBgpM2AdjRibsOutEntry.name: dellNetBgpM2AdjRibsOutEntry
dellNetBgpM2AdjRibsOutEntry.description: List of BGP routes that have been placed into a peer's Adj-Ribs-Out.

dellNetBgpM2AdjRibsOutIndex.name: dellNetBgpM2AdjRibsOutIndex
dellNetBgpM2AdjRibsOutIndex.description: Certain extensions to BGP permit multiple instance of a per afi, per safi prefix to be advertised to a peer. This object allows the enumeration of them.

dellNetBgpM2AdjRibsOutRoute.name: dellNetBgpM2AdjRibsOutRoute
dellNetBgpM2AdjRibsOutRoute.description: This object points to the route in the dellNetBgpM2NlriTable that corresponds to the entry in the peer's Adj-Rib-Out. Outgoing route maps are not reflected at this point as those are part of the Update-Send process.

dellNetBgpM2PathAttrCount.name: dellNetBgpM2PathAttrCount
dellNetBgpM2PathAttrCount.description: The number of entries in the dellNetBgpM2PathAttrTable.

dellNetBgpM2PathAttrTable.name: dellNetBgpM2PathAttrTable
dellNetBgpM2PathAttrTable.description: Provides per advertised network-prefix attribute data, as advertised over a peering session.

dellNetBgpM2PathAttrEntry.name: dellNetBgpM2PathAttrEntry
dellNetBgpM2PathAttrEntry.description: Each entry contains data about a given network prefix, per-prefix and per-advertising peer.

dellNetBgpM2PathAttrOrigin.name: dellNetBgpM2PathAttrOrigin
dellNetBgpM2PathAttrOrigin.description: The ultimate origin of the path information.

dellNetBgpM2PathAttrNextHopAddrType.name: dellNetBgpM2PathAttrNextHopAddrType
dellNetBgpM2PathAttrNextHopAddrType.description: The address family of the address for the border router that should be used to access the destination network.

dellNetBgpM2PathAttrNextHop.name: dellNetBgpM2PathAttrNextHop
dellNetBgpM2PathAttrNextHop.description: The address of the border router that should be used to access the destination network. This address is the nexthop address received in the UPDATE packet. The address family of this object will be the same as that of the prefix in this row. Note that for RFC2545 style double nexthops, this object will always contain the global scope nexthop. dellNetBgpM2LinkLocalNextHopTable will contain the linklocal scope nexthop. In the case that the mechanism documented in draft-kato-bgp-ipv6-link-local-00.txt is used and only a link local nexthop has been sent, , dellNetBgpM2LinkLocalNextHopPresent will be false and dellNetBgpM2PathAttrNextHop will contain the link local nexthop.

dellNetBgpM2PathAttrMedPresent.name: dellNetBgpM2PathAttrMedPresent
dellNetBgpM2PathAttrMedPresent.description: Whether or not the MED value is present. If it is not present, the dellNetBgpM2PathAttrMed object has no useful value and should be set to 0.

dellNetBgpM2PathAttrMed.name: dellNetBgpM2PathAttrMed
dellNetBgpM2PathAttrMed.description: This metric is used to discriminate between multiple exit points to an adjacent autonomous system.

dellNetBgpM2PathAttrLocalPrefPresent.name: dellNetBgpM2PathAttrLocalPrefPresent
dellNetBgpM2PathAttrLocalPrefPresent.description: Whether or not the LocalPref value is present. If it is not present, the dellNetBgpM2PathAttrLocalPref object has no useful value and should be set to 0.

dellNetBgpM2PathAttrLocalPref.name: dellNetBgpM2PathAttrLocalPref
dellNetBgpM2PathAttrLocalPref.description: The originating BGP4 speakers degree of preference for an advertised route.

dellNetBgpM2PathAttrAtomicAggregate.name: dellNetBgpM2PathAttrAtomicAggregate
dellNetBgpM2PathAttrAtomicAggregate.description: When this object is set to atomicAggregatePresent, the ATOMIC_AGGREGATE Path Attribute is present and indicates that the NLRI MUST NOT be made more specific.

dellNetBgpM2PathAttrAggregatorAS.name: dellNetBgpM2PathAttrAggregatorAS
dellNetBgpM2PathAttrAggregatorAS.description: The AS number of the last BGP4 speaker that performed route aggregation. A value of zero (0) indicates the absence of this attribute. Note propagation of AS of zero is illegal in the Internet.

dellNetBgpM2PathAttrAggregatorAddr.name: dellNetBgpM2PathAttrAggregatorAddr
dellNetBgpM2PathAttrAggregatorAddr.description: The IP address of the last BGP4 speaker that performed route aggregation. A value of 0.0.0.0 indicates the absence of this attribute.

dellNetBgpM2AsPathCalcLength.name: dellNetBgpM2AsPathCalcLength
dellNetBgpM2AsPathCalcLength.description: This value represents the calculated length of the AS Path according to the rules of the BGP specification. This value is used in route selection.

dellNetBgpM2AsPathString.name: dellNetBgpM2AsPathString
dellNetBgpM2AsPathString.description: This is a string depicting the autonomous system path to this network which was received from the peer which advertised it. The format of the string is implementation-dependent, and should be designed for operator readability.

dellNetBgpM2AsPathIndex.name: dellNetBgpM2AsPathIndex
dellNetBgpM2AsPathIndex.description: This value is a unique index for the decomposed AS Path in the dellNetBgpM2AsPathTable. It is assigned by the agent at the point of creation of the dellNetBgpM2AsPathTable row entry. While its value is guaranteed to be unique at any time, it is otherwise opaque to the management application with respect to its value or the contiguity of dellNetBgpM2AsPathIndex row instance values across rows of the dellNetBgpM2AsPathTable.

dellNetBgpM2AsPath4byteTable.name: dellNetBgpM2AsPath4byteTable
dellNetBgpM2AsPath4byteTable.reference: draft-ietf-idr-as4bytes-04.txt - BGP support for four-octet AS number space
dellNetBgpM2AsPath4byteTable.description: This table is present for BGP speakers that support the AS 4byte specification and are functioning as a router between 2-byte and 4-byte AS space.

dellNetBgpM2AsPath4byteEntry.name: dellNetBgpM2AsPath4byteEntry
dellNetBgpM2AsPath4byteEntry.description: Each row contains the information for the AS 4-byte extension's NEW_AS_PATH and NEW_AGGREGATOR attributes.

dellNetBgpM2AsPath4bytePathPresent.name: dellNetBgpM2AsPath4bytePathPresent
dellNetBgpM2AsPath4bytePathPresent.description: This value may only be true if this BGP Speaker is functioning as a router between ASs that are in 2-byte and 4-byte AS space. If this value is true, then the NEW_AS_PATH attributes are present and the 4-byte versions of the appropriate path attributes are in this row. If this value is false, then the following values will be present in the row: dellNetBgpM2PathAttrAggregatorAS - zero (0). dellNetBgpM2AsPathCalcLength - zero (0). dellNetBgpM2AsPathString - zero (0) length string. dellNetBgpM2AsPathIndex - zero (0).

dellNetBgpM2AsPath4byteAggregatorAS.name: dellNetBgpM2AsPath4byteAggregatorAS
dellNetBgpM2AsPath4byteAggregatorAS.description: The NEW_AGGREGATOR AS number of the last BGP4 speaker that performed route aggregation. A value of zero (0) indicates the absence of this attribute. Note propagation of AS of zero is illegal in the Internet.

dellNetBgpM2AsPath4byteCalcLength.name: dellNetBgpM2AsPath4byteCalcLength
dellNetBgpM2AsPath4byteCalcLength.description: This value represents the calculated length of the NEW_AS_PATH according to the rules of the BGP specification. This value is used in route selection.

dellNetBgpM2AsPath4byteString.name: dellNetBgpM2AsPath4byteString
dellNetBgpM2AsPath4byteString.description: This is a string depicting the autonomous system path to this network which was received from the peer which advertised it. The format of the string is implementation-dependent, and should be designed for operator readability.

dellNetBgpM2AsPath4byteIndex.name: dellNetBgpM2AsPath4byteIndex
dellNetBgpM2AsPath4byteIndex.description: This value is a unique index for the decomposed AS Path in the dellNetBgpM2AsPathTable. It is assigned by the agent at the point of creation of the dellNetBgpM2AsPathTable row entry. While its value is guaranteed to be unique at any time, it is otherwise opaque to the management application with respect to its value or the contiguity of dellNetBgpM2AsPathIndex row instance values across rows of the dellNetBgpM2AsPathTable.

dellNetBgpM2AsPathTable.name: dellNetBgpM2AsPathTable
dellNetBgpM2AsPathTable.description: The BGP-4 Path Attribute AS Path Table contains the per network path (NLRI) AS PATH data received from the advertising BGP peer.

dellNetBgpM2AsPathTableEntry.name: dellNetBgpM2AsPathTableEntry
dellNetBgpM2AsPathTableEntry.description: Information about an AS path provided with a path to a network.

dellNetBgpM2AsPathSegmentIndex.name: dellNetBgpM2AsPathSegmentIndex
dellNetBgpM2AsPathSegmentIndex.description: A per-AS path segment index. This will index a set of autonomous systems in an AS path which are part of the same sequence or set (as determined by the row value of dellNetBgpM2AsPathType, which should be the same value for each dellNetBgpM2AsPathTable entry indexed by the same (dellNetBgpM2PathAttrIndex, dellNetBgpM2AsPathIndex) pair).

dellNetBgpM2AsPathElementIndex.name: dellNetBgpM2AsPathElementIndex
dellNetBgpM2AsPathElementIndex.description: A per-AS element index. This will index a particular AS within a sequence or set of autonomous systems in an AS path.

dellNetBgpM2AsPathType.name: dellNetBgpM2AsPathType
dellNetBgpM2AsPathType.description: The type of sequence in which this asPath was advertised as an attribute. Note that all asPath row instances for a given (dellNetBgpM2PathAttrIndex, dellNetBgpM2AsPathIndex) index pair will have their dellNetBgpM2AsPathType set to the same value. The values for dellNetBgpM2AsPathType are interpreted as defined in the base BGP document and the BGP AS Confederations document.

dellNetBgpM2AsPathElementValue.name: dellNetBgpM2AsPathElementValue
dellNetBgpM2AsPathElementValue.description: An AS value for an AS the related NLRI traversed in the propagation of its advertisement. This value is to be interpreted in the context of the sequence implied by dellNetBgpM2AsPathIndex and dellNetBgpM2AsPathType (and, in sequence of the other table rows with the same value of dellNetBgpM2PathAttrIndex and dellNetBgpM2AsPathIndex).

dellNetBgpM2PathAttrUnknownTable.name: dellNetBgpM2PathAttrUnknownTable
dellNetBgpM2PathAttrUnknownTable.description: The BGP-4 Path Attribute Unknown Table contains the per network path (NLRI) data on the path attributes advertised with a route but not known to the local BGP implementation or not otherwise capable of being returned from this agent.
